{
  "texts": [
    "Suppose x ∈ R for some R ∈ R k. Then there exists some i ∈ {0,..., K -1}, such that x ∈ Q(R, i).",
    "If such i can be found even, we let refine k (ρ)(x) = 1 and we let refine k (ρ)(x) = 2 otherwisefoot_3.",
    "We use the notationrefine [k] (ρ) = refine k (refine k-1 (... (refine 1 (ρ)))).For illustration, see Figure 5, where a particular instance of the function refine 1 (ρ) is indicated.Figure 5: Picture of refine 1 (ρ) in case K = 6, M = 4 and d = 2.",
    "The whole rectangle is the initial rectangle R 0.",
    "The black regions correspond to sets on which refine 1 (ρ) = 1 and the white regions correspond to sets on which refine 1 (ρ) = 2."
  ]
}